---
import { getCollection } from "astro:content";
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import { siteConfig } from "../site.config";

const logs = await getCollection("updates");
---

<BaseLayout
  title="关于/更新日志 | 异环攻略站"
  description="了解异环攻略站的内容范围、维护方式、信息来源、更新日志与联系方式。"
  jsonLd={{ "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "AboutPage", name: "关于异环攻略站" }}
>
  <article class="prose lang-zh max-w-none">
    <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-neon" data-i18n="about.kicker">About</p>
    <h1 data-i18n="about.title">关于异环攻略站</h1>
    <p data-i18n="about.desc">
      {siteConfig.fullName} 是一个面向《异环》（Neverness to Everness / NTE）玩家的中文攻略与资料整理网站。本站关注角色培养、配队思路、地图探索、异象委托、搜打撤玩法、版本动态与实用工具，目标是把分散的游戏信息整理成容易检索、能够直接用于开荒和养成规划的内容。
    </p>

    <h2>我们是谁，为什么做这个站</h2>
    <p>
      本站由普通玩家维护，不隶属于游戏官方。建立这个站的原因很简单：开放世界 RPG 的资料经常分散在公告、社区讨论、视频评论和玩家截图里，新玩家很难快速判断“我现在该练谁、该刷什么、该怎么查漏”。我们希望把这些信息整理成结构清楚、能被搜索到、也方便手机阅读的中文攻略。
    </p>
    <p>
      我们更重视可执行的经验：角色页会写定位和循环，地图页会写分层路线，工具页会解释参数含义，版本内容会提醒哪些结论需要复查。即使部分数值会随版本变化，页面也会尽量保留判断依据，让玩家知道为什么这样安排。
    </p>

    <h2 data-i18n="about.content">本站提供什么内容</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>角色攻略：定位、技能机制、装备词条、觉醒节点、配队和实战循环。</li>
      <li>地图探索：传送点、收集路线、隐藏机制、异象委托与区域跑图建议。</li>
      <li>新手指南：资源规划、每日优先级、开荒误区和版本环境变化。</li>
      <li>工具页面：抽卡概率、养成规划等在浏览器本地运行的辅助工具。</li>
      <li>版本动态：围绕新活动、新任务、新角色和玩法变化整理重点信息。</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 data-i18n="about.source">内容来源与维护方式</h2>
    <p>
      本站内容主要来自公开游戏信息、站点编辑整理、测试体验、玩家反馈以及官方公告的二次归纳。攻略会尽量标注更新时间，并在版本更新、角色调整或玩法机制变化后进行修订。由于游戏内容可能继续调整，页面建议仅作为参考，关键数值请以游戏内实际显示和官方公告为准。
    </p>
    <p>
      当我们使用官方宣传图、商店页截图或游戏内截图时，会尽量放在攻略语境中作为说明配图，而不是作为独立素材分发。若有来源、版权或署名问题，欢迎通过联系页面反馈。
    </p>

    <h2>内容质量与广告审核准备</h2>
    <p>
      为了避免低价值或内容贫乏页面，本站会优先发布能够解决具体问题的长篇攻略，例如角色培养、地图分层补漏、异象委托排查、资源规划和工具使用说明。列表页用于组织导航，正文页则尽量提供可执行步骤、判断依据、常见误区和版本复查建议，而不是只堆砌关键词或复制公告。
    </p>
    <p>
      当页面内容过短、信息重复或版本依据不足时，本站会选择扩写、合并、延后发布或从导航中移除。广告位不会覆盖正文、不会阻挡导航，也不会要求读者点击广告才能继续浏览内容。
    </p>

    <h2 data-i18n="about.independence">独立性说明</h2>
    <p>
      本站为玩家自建资料站，并非《异环》官方网站，也不代表开发商、发行商或相关权利方的官方立场。本站使用的游戏名称、角色、图片和相关素材版权归其合法权利人所有，使用目的为攻略说明、评论和资料索引。
    </p>

    <h2 data-i18n="about.contact">联系我们</h2>
    <p>
      如需反馈攻略错误、提出内容建议、请求删除版权相关内容或咨询隐私问题，请访问 <a href="/contact/">联系我们</a> 页面，或发送邮件至 <a href={`mailto:${siteConfig.contactEmail}`}>{siteConfig.contactEmail}</a>。
    </p>
  </article>

  <article class="prose lang-en max-w-none">
    <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-neon">About</p>
    <h1>About NTE Guide</h1>
    <p>
      NTE Guide is a fan-made guide and reference site for Neverness to Everness players. It organizes character builds, team ideas, map exploration, anomaly commissions, version updates and browser-based planning tools into pages that are easy to search and use during progression.
    </p>

    <h2>Who Maintains This Site</h2>
    <p>
      This site is maintained by regular players and is not affiliated with the official game team. We built it because open-world RPG information is often scattered across announcements, community posts, video comments and screenshots, which makes it hard for new players to decide what to build, farm or revisit.
    </p>
    <p>
      We focus on actionable guide value. Character pages explain roles and rotations, map pages describe layered cleanup routes, tools explain their parameters, and version-sensitive pages show what should be rechecked after updates.
    </p>

    <h2>What This Site Covers</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Character guides: role, mechanics, stats, awakening order, teams and combat rotations.</li>
      <li>Map exploration: teleports, collection routes, hidden mechanics, anomaly commissions and district routing.</li>
      <li>Beginner guides: resource planning, daily priorities, progression mistakes and version review notes.</li>
      <li>Tools: local browser calculators for pull budgets and growth planning.</li>
      <li>Version updates: practical summaries around events, characters and gameplay changes.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Sources and Maintenance</h2>
    <p>
      Content is based on public game information, editorial organization, testing experience, player feedback and official announcements. Guides are marked with update dates and revised when characters, routes, rules or reward structures change.
    </p>
    <p>
      Official artwork, store-page screenshots or in-game screenshots are used only as guide context, commentary or indexing material. Copyright and attribution issues can be reported through the contact page.
    </p>

    <h2>Content Quality and Ad Review Readiness</h2>
    <p>
      To avoid thin or low-value pages, we prioritize long-form guides that solve specific player problems, such as character investment, layered map cleanup, anomaly troubleshooting, resource planning and tool usage. Index pages organize navigation, while article pages provide steps, reasoning, mistakes to avoid and version review points.
    </p>
    <p>
      Pages that are too short, repetitive or unsupported by version evidence are expanded, merged, delayed or removed from navigation. Ads should not cover content, block navigation or require clicks before reading.
    </p>

    <h2>Independence Notice</h2>
    <p>
      This is an unofficial fan-made guide site. It does not represent the official position of the developer, publisher or any rights holder. Game names, characters, images and related assets belong to their lawful owners and are used for guide commentary and reference.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>
      For corrections, content suggestions, copyright requests or privacy questions, use the <a href="/contact/">contact page</a> or email <a href={`mailto:${siteConfig.contactEmail}`}>{siteConfig.contactEmail}</a>.
    </p>
  </article>

  <section class="mt-10">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-zinc-950 dark:text-white" data-i18n="about.changelog">更新日志</h2>
    <div class="mt-4 space-y-4">
    {
      logs.map((l) => (
        <article class="card">
          <p class="text-xs text-zinc-500">{l.data.date}</p>
          <h2 class="mt-2 font-bold">{l.data.title}</h2>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-zinc-400">{l.data.description}</p>
        </article>
      ))
    }
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
